                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/104: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-25T17:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 26—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Keilhauer has left for the United States with full powers from the
                    Salvadorean Government to sign loan contract on terms already agreed to. It is
                    expected Government will get another quarter million dollars temporary loan
                    Keith interests to tie [<hi rend="italic">tide?</hi>] it over until definite
                    loan arranged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
